
[1]accredit

   ACCRED'IT, v.t. [L. ad and credo, to believe, or give faith to. See
   Credit.]

   To give credit, authority, or reputation; to accredit an envoy, is to
   receive him in his public character, and give him credit and rank
   accordingly.
